<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="552" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,511,654,714]" box="[151,267,689,714]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,258,689,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[155,1411,206,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Megaselia bangiensis sp. n. male: 1—frons; 2—thorax and abdomen; 3–5—hypopygium; 3—left face; 4— hypandrium; 5—right face; 6—hind femur." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607524/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Figs 1–6</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,761,786]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Description.</emphasis>
Male only. The specimen is somewhat faded and in particular the wings beyond the costa are so bleached that neither the thin veins nor the boundaries of the membrane beyond the costa are discernible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,1902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">
Frons as 
<figureCitation box="[299,363,833,858]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[155,1411,206,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Megaselia bangiensis sp. n. male: 1—frons; 2—thorax and abdomen; 3–5—hypopygium; 3—left face; 4— hypandrium; 5—right face; 6—hind femur." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607524/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, with 130–136 hairs and dense but very small microtrichia. SAs very unequal. The antials lower on frons than anterolaterals, and about as far from upper SAs as either is from an AL bristle. Mediolateral row convex, with the mediolaterals clearly below pre-ocellars but otherwise the four bristles about equally spaced. Cheek with two bristles and jowl with two, which are a little longer but equally fine. Postpedicels yellow, without SPS vesicles. Palps yellow, at most a fifth as broad as postpedicel but about 1.4 times as long as breadth of latter, with seven bristles, the 2–3 apical ones being longest, and 2–3 hairs. Labrum pale and about 0.7 times as wide as a postpedicel. Labella paler than palps and with numerous short spinules below. Thorax as 
<figureCitation box="[1238,1312,1049,1074]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[155,1411,206,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Megaselia bangiensis sp. n. male: 1—frons; 2—thorax and abdomen; 3–5—hypopygium; 3—left face; 4— hypandrium; 5—right face; 6—hind femur." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607524/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
, with two notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these. Mesopleuron bare. Scutellum with an anterior pair of hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal tergites as 
<figureCitation box="[754,831,1121,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[155,1411,206,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Megaselia bangiensis sp. n. male: 1—frons; 2—thorax and abdomen; 3–5—hypopygium; 3—left face; 4— hypandrium; 5—right face; 6—hind femur." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607524/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
, with moderate hairs some of which are longer posterolaterally, especially on T2 and T6 (
<figureCitation box="[636,706,1157,1182]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[155,1411,206,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Megaselia bangiensis sp. n. male: 1—frons; 2—thorax and abdomen; 3–5—hypopygium; 3—left face; 4— hypandrium; 5—right face; 6—hind femur." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607524/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Venter (
<figureCitation box="[821,890,1157,1182]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[155,1411,206,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Megaselia bangiensis sp. n. male: 1—frons; 2—thorax and abdomen; 3–5—hypopygium; 3—left face; 4— hypandrium; 5—right face; 6—hind femur." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607524/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) with hairs on segments 3–6 at least as long as those on tergites. Hypopygium (
<figureCitation box="[511,610,1193,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[155,1411,206,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Megaselia bangiensis sp. n. male: 1—frons; 2—thorax and abdomen; 3–5—hypopygium; 3—left face; 4— hypandrium; 5—right face; 6—hind femur." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607524/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Figs 3–5</figureCitation>
) with a pale anal tube. Anal tube length shorter than epandrium. Hairs on proctiger and cercus longer than hairs on epandrium. Hypandrium left lobe pale (
<figureCitation box="[1099,1170,1229,1254]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[155,1411,206,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Megaselia bangiensis sp. n. male: 1—frons; 2—thorax and abdomen; 3–5—hypopygium; 3—left face; 4— hypandrium; 5—right face; 6—hind femur." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607524/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) and with microtrichia ending before its tapered tip. The right lobe is vestigial (
<figureCitation box="[789,858,1265,1290]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[155,1411,206,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Megaselia bangiensis sp. n. male: 1—frons; 2—thorax and abdomen; 3–5—hypopygium; 3—left face; 4— hypandrium; 5—right face; 6—hind femur." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607524/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Legs brown to yellowish brown. Fore tarsus with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–4 and 5 clearly longer than 4. Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.8 times its length. Hairs below basal half of hind femur (
<figureCitation box="[887,955,1337,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[155,1411,206,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,195,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Megaselia bangiensis sp. n. male: 1—frons; 2—thorax and abdomen; 3–5—hypopygium; 3—left face; 4— hypandrium; 5—right face; 6—hind femur." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607524/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) longer than those of anteroventral row of outer half. Hind tibia with 11–12 only moderately differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wing length and costal index not discernible. Costal ratios 1.8: 1.5: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[370,472,1446,1470]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" unit="mm" value="0.04">0.04 mm</quantity>
long. Hair at base of vein 3. With 3 axillary bristles, the outer being 
<quantity box="[1272,1437,1445,1470]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" unit="mm" value="0.055" valueMax="0.06" valueMin="0.05">0.05–0.06 mm</quantity>
long. Sc obscure and not reaching R1. Thick veins yellowish brown (wing beyond costa obscure). Haltere knob brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1134,1553,1578]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" type="etymology">
